Filter selected orgdb columns by gene-type

Source: R/rnaseq_related.R
dot-filter_orgdb_by_genetype.Rd

Filter selected orgdb columns by gene-type

Usage

.filter_orgdb_by_genetype(
  orgdb,
  col_genetype = "GENETYPE",
  feature_type = "protein-coding",
  col_return = "ENTREZID"
)

Arguments

orgdb

an OrgDB

col_genetype

a column name to filter by the value given in feature_type

feature_type

a string denoting value to filter the column mentioned by col_genetype.

col_return

a character string denoting a column to return from an OrgDB.

Value

a character string of the column mentioned in col_return.

Examples

.filter_orgdb_by_genetype(orgdb = org.Hs.eg.db::org.Hs.eg.db ,col_return = "ENTREZID",feature_type = "snRNA")
